

Gao Qiufu, former vice president of Xinhua News Agency, recently published his prose collection, titled "Colorful Africa-- A Mysterious Continent written by Xinhua journalist".

The collection, published by the Xinhua Publishing House, is one of the a few Chinese-language writings focusing on Africa.

The collection, in 240,000 words, consists of more than 70 prose, written by Gao during 1980 to 2003, on the natural conditions, social customs and history of the Sub-Sahara Africa.

Gao worked in Africa for more than seven years. He traveled and made reports in numerous African places. As a journalist and expert specialized in African issues, he presents his experiences and understanding on Africa's culture and social customs in his prose.

